This week will introduce the concept of machine learning and describe the four major areas of places it can be used in sports analytics. 
The machine learning pipeline will be discussed, as well as some common issues one runs into when using machine learning for sports analytics.

Learning Objectives
  Understand the issue of overfitting
  Understand the general stages of machine learning: data acquisition, feature engineering, predictive modeling, and evaluation
  Understand the difference between classification, clustering, and regression, and how they relate to one another
  Understand what machine learning is and how it differs from other statistical approaches
